    "recap_headline": "Oregon State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "IRVINE, Calif.\n\u2013\nEaston Talt's\nsecond home run of the season prompted an Oregon State onslaught en route to the Beavers' 9-5 win over UC Irvine Sunday at Cicerone Field. The win gave Oregon State a three-game sweep over their Big West Conference rivals.\nTalt, with the Beavers trailing 2-0 after five innings, homered to right on a 1-1 pitch to open the sixth inning. Prior to his at bat, Oregon State (17-5) had recorded just one hit, on a fly ball single by Talt to open the game.\nThe home run opened the floodgates.\nAJ Singer\nput the Beavers ahead for good with a two-run single in the sixth, which was followed by a two-run double off the wall in right center by\nPaul Vazquez\n.\nSinger hit a sacrifice fly in the seventh, a key RBI as Tommy Farmer hit a two-run home run in the bottom half of the frame to pull the Anteaters (9-14) to within two.\nThe Beavers, however, scored three more in the eighth, highlighted by\nBryson Glassco's\nfirst home run at Oregon State, en route to the eventual 9-5 win.\nOregon State recorded 11 of its 12 hits in addition to all nine runs from the sixth inning on. Talt,\nBryce Hubbard\nand\nJacob Galloway\nall recorded two hits in the series finale.\nTrey Morris\n, the first of three relievers on the afternoon, was the recipient of the run support. He went 2 1/3 innings, allowing Farmer's home run while striking out four. He got the win, the first of his collegiate career.\nEric Segura\nstarted and tied a career single-game high with eight strikeouts in four innings. He gave way to Morris in the fifth and allowed two runs on two hits.\nZach Edwards\ntossed two scoreless innings, striking out three for his first save of 2026. OSU, as a staff, recorded 15 strikeouts and 45 for the three-game series.\nFinnegan Wall was sharp for UC Irvine through five innings, but was the pitcher of record when the Beavers went ahead in the sixth. He gave up four runs on four hits while striking out four. Wall took the loss to drop to 1-1.\nOregon State remains in California for a couple more days as the Beavers prepare to take on USC Tuesday afternoon at Dedeaux Field. First pitch is slated for 1 p.m. PT.\nFollow Us On Social\nFor more information on the Oregon State baseball team, follow the club's official X account at X.com/BeaverBaseball, by Facebook at Facebook.com/OregonStateBaseball, at BeaverBaseball.OSUBeavers.com on BlueSky or on Instagram at Instagram.com/BeaverBaseball.\nOUR MISSION\nOregon State Athletics strives to Build Excellent Authentic Visionary Student-Athletes (Go BEAVS).",
